=== Pronunciation ===
[[Category:Hebrew language]]
נוּח / nûach / noo'-akh
=== Etymology ===

A primitive root; 
=== Verb ===
to [[rest]], that is, settle down; used in a great variety of applications, literally and figuratively, intransitively, transitively and causatively (to dwell, stay, let fall, place, let alone, withdraw, give comfort, etc.): - cease, be confederate, lay, let down, (be) quiet, remain, (cause to, be at, give, have, make to) rest, set down. Compare H3241.